
Overview of verb recuperate

The verb recuperate has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                   
1. recover, recoup, recuperate -- (regain or make up for; "recuperate one's losses")
2. recover, go back, recuperate -- (regain a former condition after a financial loss; "We expect the stocks to recover to $2.90"; "The company managed to recuperate")
3. recuperate -- (restore to good health or strength)
4. recuperate, recover, convalesce -- (get over an illness or shock; "The patient is recuperating")
